<object id="GUID-252B2697-9453-462D-9F80-B30C00600045" class="- topic/object "><desc class="- topic/desc "><p class="- topic/p ">Check pressure leakage </p></desc><param name="testid" value="076004" class="- topic/param "/><param name="target" value="NIL" class="- topic/param "/><param name="axmodule" value="None" class="- topic/param "/></object> 
</p></section><section id="GUID-1156E15C-FA11-42F7-80CE-F9823F371FA9" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Function</title><p class="- topic/p ">This test checks for air pressure leaks in the printer. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-3FF66866-E0E6-4181-B99D-C4324DE0F267" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Description</title><p class="- topic/p ">The pressure of the system is set to -20 mbar. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">When this pressure is reached the pump is stopped and the pressure valves are closed. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The pressure is relaxed for 1 minute. In the 2<sup class="+ topic/ph hi-d/sup ">nd</sup> part of the test the pressure leakage is measured. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">- 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The test fails if 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> the pressure drops too fast within 2 minutes. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">the printhead temperature is not stable. 
</p></li></ul></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-F76221B5-E49A-45FA-A4FE-0789E59F6EBD.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>SDS</linktext></link></linkpool><link keyref="07DIAGIDENTIFYLEAKAGE001" class="- topic/link " href="GUID-D8F4A0EA-5E9A-4C9A-8EC6-8982C873948E.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext ">07 How to identify a leakage of the pressure system</linktext></link></related-links></task>